I'd like to take this opportunity to give credit where credit is due. My words paint the pictures past of John Collison aka &quot;Cajun&quot;, a marine who served from 69-71 as a doorgunner. He is not alone in that his memories will forever burn deep ... wanting to share, but knowing the sting of judgement and misunderstanding. I am only the tool by which he is able to express his deepest thoughts of a past that has been carefully locked away. <br><br>
Thank you again for this opportunity to share, it has made a difference.<br><br>
*a warm, heartfelt smile of gratitude* 
